The paper focuses on the task of visual question answering (VQA), which involves understanding both visual and textual information. This suggests that the paper could belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) or natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses changes to the model architecture and learning rate schedule, which are common techniques in the field of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of ensembling also suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper involves working with large datasets and improving performance, which could fall under the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category.
